00:25:34,800 --> 00:25:39,720
We're actually the tariffs that are most similar to the ones that we are seeing today, which were global tariffs.

375
00:25:40,080 --> 00:25:49,880
And in 1930, the market fell 28.5 percent and that was on the back of the market coming off sharply in 1929.

376
00:25:50,440 --> 00:25:57,920
And of course, that was really driven by, you know, an incredible amount of margin that was made available to the market margin calls.

377
00:25:58,240 --> 00:26:03,200
And then central banks sort of tightening into that period when the market was collapsing.

378
00:26:03,520 --> 00:26:12,680
So between 1929 and then having the Smoot-Hawley tariffs in 1930, it was a really harsh period for the market over a two and a half year period there.

379
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:22,280
But the tariffs had such a negative impact on the markets that there wasn't another president until Richard Nixon that launched tariffs.

380
00:26:22,280 --> 00:26:23,760
And that was during the Nixon shock.

